This phenomenon is called metonymy. It is a feature of the English language.
To people who work with widgets and widget controllers all day, this is just a handy abbreviation, but for people who are just learning about widgets and widget controllers, this shorthand just adds to the confusion.
The truth is quite the opposite. Part-to-whole metonymy comes naturally to all English speakers, not just proponents of the model-view-controller model.
