Early in my career, the company I worked for did this thing I always wish would have caught on. In lieu of code reviews, each programmer would hand off his code to another and that programmer would write the comments for it.
The result was that the comments were written from the point of view of someone trying to understand the code. The same point of view as the person who would later read them.
